article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 77, Kennesaw State 72
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Marc Davis scored a game-high 30 points and grabbed 3 rebounds, and Maryland-Eastern Shore defeated Kennesaw 77-72 Tuesday night. Aleksandar Popovic pulled down a game-high 17 rebounds for UMES (2-9, 0-1 MEAC). Ed Tyson added 25 points. Ronell Wooten scored a team-high 26 points for Kennesaw (2-6).Tanner Jacobs grabbed 12 rebounds.
